# File: .env.deploy.example
# Description: Template for .env.deploy — the (git-ignored) credentials + target file that
#   scripts/deploy-verpex.sh reads to upload the production dist/ to the Verpex shared host.
#   Copy this to `.env.deploy`, fill in the real values, and keep `.env.deploy` OUT of git
#   (.gitignore covers it). NEVER commit real credentials. The deploy script fails loudly if
#   .env.deploy is missing or if VERPEX_REMOTE_PATH is unset — there is no hardcoded fallback.
# Author: Libor Ballaty (with assistant)
# Created: 2026-07-10
#
# Operator steps to go live (STAGED release — see docs/MULTI-AGENT-WORKFLOW.md §7):
#   1. cp .env.deploy.example .env.deploy   &&   fill in the values below (BOTH remote paths).
#   2. Dry run (no creds):  bash scripts/deploy-verpex.sh --target staging --dry-run
#   3. npm run deploy:staging     → uploads to testfalamadeira ; VERIFY it in a browser.
#   4. npm run deploy:approve     → records approval of the staged git commit.
#   5. npm run deploy:production  → uploads to falamadeira (REFUSED unless THIS commit was staged+approved).
#   6. Supabase dashboard (project gxlrmdfqcqimwwplrdgd) → Authentication → URL Configuration:
#        Site URL / Redirect URLs must include BOTH:
#          https://falamadeira.searchingfool.com/**  AND  https://testfalamadeira.searchingfool.com/**
#      (magic-link / OAuth redirects break on an origin until it's allow-listed.)

# --- Connection ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SFTP/SSH host for the Verpex account (e.g. host.verpex.example or the server IP).
VERPEX_HOST=

# SSH/SFTP username for the account.
VERPEX_USER=

# Auth: EITHER a private key path (preferred) OR a password. If VERPEX_SSH_KEY is set it is used
# and the password is ignored. Password auth over sftp/scp is non-interactive only if sshpass is
# installed; the key path is the recommended, sshpass-free route.
VERPEX_SSH_KEY=
VERPEX_PASS=

# Optional SSH/SFTP port (default 22).
VERPEX_PORT=22

# --- Targets (SCOPED — the ONLY directories we ever write to) -----------------------------------
# Two document roots on the SAME account (staged release, INFRA-4). deploy-verpex.sh guards each:
# staging MUST be a *testfalamadeira* dir; production MUST be a falamadeira (and NOT testfalamadeira)
# dir — so neither target can ever write into the other's directory. Empty = loud refusal.
#
# PRODUCTION — the falamadeira.searchingfool.com document root
# (e.g. /home/<user>/falamadeira.searchingfool.com):
VERPEX_REMOTE_PATH=
#
# STAGING / pre-release — the testfalamadeira.searchingfool.com document root
# (e.g. /home/<user>/testfalamadeira.searchingfool.com):
VERPEX_STAGING_REMOTE_PATH=
